  "prompt": "What does \"subject to availability\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Subject to availability\" is a phrase often used to indicate that a product, service, or offer is not guaranteed to be in stock or accessible at the time of your request. It implies that fulfillment depends on current inventory levels or availability and that certain items may run out of stock or may not be available for everyone who wishes to purchase or use them. This phrase is commonly used in contexts such as hotel bookings, restaurant reservations, product sales, and promotional offers, and it advises customers to check for the availability at the time of their request.",
